LDTEXT:
@18:28 - plant locked out and shutdown on contact chamber 1 low and Lolo alarms, along with a series of low lift alarms.  Contacted Dan B from Lexsan, he will return to site to investigate
@19:11 - Adjusted chlorinator #6 dosage factor from 58 to 60% and chlorinator #8 from 120 to 150%
- Tested chlorination system with Clearwell SV 2 running in D1 - confirmed chlorine dosing by opening rotameter on chlorinator #6.  Placed chlorine system back to auto. 
@19:45 - opened train #3 inlet valve to test low lift pump 1 - caused tank level high and hihi alarms due to water overflowing to waste tanks (intentionally) 
@19:52 - stopped low lift P1, no alarms occurred this time during the pump run.  Lexsan has returned to site, waiting for Eaton to arrive to continue troubleshooting with Multi Lin 
- @20:37 Adjusted chlorinator #6 dosage factor back to 60%, as the recirculation pump has brought chlorine residuals back to better levels
- Stephen B will continue in his log entry
